This program was developed using python 3.7 and utilizes inbuilt functions that are not available on previous versions.
It is advisable to ensure that this program is ran using this version of python.

Dependencies and versions required to run this program:
certifi==2019.11.28
chardet==3.0.4
idna==2.8
joblib==0.14.0
nltk==3.4.5
numpy==1.17.4
pandas==0.25.3
pycorenlp==0.3.0
python-dateutil==2.8.1
pytz==2019.3
requests==2.22.0
scikit-learn==0.21.3
scipy==1.3.3
six==1.13.0
sklearn==0.0
urllib3==1.25.7

It is advisable that the csv files (training.csv and test.csv) are in the same directory as the python files,
otherwise a slight modification to the code will be required.


Finally, to run this program, please run the Main.py file.
When the program is run, the user will be prompted to take action and input the classification type they would like to perform.
Either 'gender' or 'character' must be typed in and returned to the program.

To run the non optimal model using the individual unigram and bigram tokens as features represented in many hot arrays, please run the Old_main.py file:
- However, be advised that running this file may take a considerably longer time (in comparison to Main.py)